{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":98280,"duration_api_ms":141576,"num_turns":5,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"ae79fd64-b908-4c2b-ac54-0a32eb483a37","total_cost_usd":0.41197110000000003,"usage":{"input_tokens":2911,"cache_creation_input_tokens":26819,"cache_read_input_tokens":75684,"output_tokens":3308,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":26819,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":102,"outputTokens":6928,"cacheReadInputTokens":366671,"cacheCreationInputTokens":30277,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.10925535,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":2911,"outputTokens":3308,"cacheReadInputTokens":75684,"cacheCreationInputTokens":26819,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.30271575,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"Reviewed 5 amendments against the actual source code. Three address real bugs (backoff off-by-one x2, whitespace API key inconsistency), one addresses a real test race condition with an existing mitigation pattern available, and one identifies a genuine resource leak in tmux cleanup. All five amendments identify legitimate defects confirmed by code inspection.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-10-d56bff07","decision":"accept","rationale":"Confirmed by code inspection. cursor.attempt starts at 1 (StageCursor::initial()), and backoff_for_attempt() returns Duration::ZERO when attempt==0 (retry_policy.rs:107-108). So backoff_for_attempt(1-1) = backoff_for_attempt(0) = ZERO on the first retry. This is an off-by-one that makes the first retry immediate, shifting all subsequent delays down one step. Using backoff_for_attempt(cursor.attempt) directly would give the intended 1-indexed behavior where attempt=1 gets the base delay."},{"amendment_id":"fr-10-91429d88","decision":"accept","rationale":"Confirmed: the two OpenRouter API key tests use unsafe env var manipulation without a mutex, while the codebase already has a lock_path_mutex() pattern in tests/unit/env_test_support.rs specifically for synchronizing env var access in parallel test threads. The _guard/restore pattern is insufficient because cargo runs test functions across threads. An OPENROUTER_API_KEY mutex analogous to PATH_MUTEX is the correct fix and follows established project conventions."},{"amendment_id":"fr-10-447afeb1","decision":"accept","rationale":"This is the same bug as fr-10-d56bff07 with additional detail about the 1-indexed contract of backoff_for_attempt(). The analysis is correct: the method at retry_policy.rs:106-113 documents 1-indexed semantics where attempt=1 yields backoff_base. The -1 adjustment at engine.rs:4620 breaks this contract, making the first retry immediate (0 delay) and shifting all subsequent delays down one level. This is particularly harmful for rate-limit recovery where the first backoff matters most."},{"amendment_id":"fr-10-722690d1","decision":"accept","rationale":"Confirmed by code inspection. cancel() calls take_active_session() at line 622 which removes the session from tracking immediately, before attempting SIGTERM/SIGKILL/kill-session cleanup (lines 626-677). The timeout branch at line 537 discards the cancel() result with `let _ =`. If cleanup fails after tracking removal, the tmux session/process remains alive but is no longer tracked — there is no way to retry cleanup later. While the timeout branch does return an error (not success as the amendment loosely states), the real issue is the resource leak: an orphaned tmux session with no tracking handle. The fix should either defer tracking removal until after cleanup succeeds, or log/surface the cleanup failure."},{"amendment_id":"fr-10-182ad707","decision":"accept","rationale":"Confirmed: process_backend.rs:802 uses `.filter(|k| !k.is_empty())` while openrouter_backend.rs:73 uses `!value.trim().is_empty()`. A whitespace-only OPENROUTER_API_KEY (e.g., ' ') passes the process backend check, bypasses the terminal BinaryNotFound error, and gets sent to the subprocess where it will fail as a transport error eligible for retries. The HTTP adapter correctly rejects it as terminal. Since process is the default adapter (agent_execution_builder.rs:53-74), this inconsistency affects the production path. The fix is trivial: add .trim() to the process backend's is_empty() checks to match the HTTP adapter."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"4f8a1d61-a08c-44f3-b692-654454643a38"}
